{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012vyPfSAaSM61U9vTr9Eyqx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Prometheus reports `mongodb_up = 1`. Here's a summary of what was deployed:\n\n**What was done:**\n\n1. **Secret** `mongodb-exporter-credentials` (mongodb namespace) — holds the replica-set connection URI `mongodb://admin-user:…@<all-3-members>/admin?replicaSet=mongodb-replica`. The multi-host URI ensures the exporter follows primary elections without reconnection failures.\n\n2. **Deployment** `mongodb-exporter` (mongodb namespace) — runs `percona/mongodb_exporter:0.40` (already cached locally). Reads the URI from the Secret and exposes metrics on port 9216 with `--collect-all --compatible-mode`.\n\n3. **Service** `mongodb-exporter` (mongodb namespace) — ClusterIP service routing to port 9216, reachable at `mongodb-exporter.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:9216`.\n\n4. **ConfigMap** `prometheus-config` (monitoring namespace) — added a `mongodb` scrape job targeting the exporter service. Prometheus was reloaded via `/-/reload`.\n\n**Verification:** Prometheus shows the `mongodb` target as `up` and `mongodb_up = 1` with metrics from the actual `mongodb-replica` replica set (including all 3 member states)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":321,"cache_read_input_tokens":41622,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":321},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"05ed0d10-a4b5-40e8-a6f4-eb7f23eb252d","uuid":"2457935e-d5c6-43ac-8be1-5aecbfdb15c9","request_id":"req_011Ccf7eSyHDgiMmiXVbrY3v"}
